        <p class="philosophy__body fade-up fade-up-delay-1">I own the property. You make monthly payments directly to me. When the note is paid off, the deed transfers to you. No bank, no lender, no approval committee.</p>
        <p class="philosophy__body fade-up fade-up-delay-1" style="margin-top:1rem;">Every listing has the APN, GPS coordinates, and county zoning on record. Look it up before you buy. I'd do the same.</p>
        <p class="philosophy__body fade-up fade-up-delay-1" style="margin-top:1rem;">Have questions before you commit? Call me directly: <a href="tel:7069630017" style="color:var(--color-terra);font-weight:600;">706-963-0017</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="philosophy__cards">
        <div class="philo-card fade-up">
          <div class="philo-card__icon">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>I own it before I sell it</h3>
            <p>Every property in my inventory is already purchased. I'm not listing other people's land. It's mine to sell, on my terms, directly to you.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="philo-card fade-up fade-up-delay-1">
          <div class="philo-card__icon">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="1" x2="12" y2="23"/><path d="M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 0 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 7H6"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>The price comes from real sales</h3>
            <p>Not Zillow estimates. Not county assessed value. Actual comparable transactions from actual closed sales in the same area.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="philo-card fade-up fade-up-delay-2">
          <div class="philo-card__icon">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>I'll tell you what I don't know</h3>
            <p>If something on a property is uncertain, the listing says so. I'd rather lose a sale than promise something I can't back up.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHO IS THIS FOR ── #}
<section class="for-section">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="eyebrow for-section__eyebrow fade-up">Who Buys This Way</span>
    <h2 class="heading-xl for-section__title fade-up fade-up-delay-1">This land is for you if...</h2>
    <div class="for-grid">
      <div class="for-card fade-up">
        <p class="for-card__title">You've never bought land before.</p>
        <p class="for-card__body">You're not sure if you're doing something wrong. You're not. If you can make a monthly payment, you can do this. The process takes less than a week from first call to signed contract.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="for-card fade-up fade-up-delay-1">
        <p class="for-card__title">You're done building someone else's equity.</p>
        <p class="for-card__body">Rent goes out every month and nothing comes back. Land is a different kind of ownership. No landlord, no lease renewal, no approval needed from anyone but you.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="for-card fade-up fade-up-delay-1">
        <p class="for-card__title">You want something to hold long-term.</p>
        <p class="for-card__body">No tenants. No maintenance calls. No drama. Land in growing markets tends to get more valuable over time. You buy it, you hold it, you own it outright when the note is done.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="for-card fade-up fade-up-delay-2">
        <p class="for-card__title">The bank already said no.</p>
        <p class="for-card__body">Credit history, employment gaps, self-employment income. None of that matters here. What matters is a down payment and a monthly payment you can actually make.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

